==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Third-rail system
<hw>Third-rail system</hw>. <fld>(Electric Railways)</fld> <def>A system
in which a third rail is used for carrying the current for operating the
motors, the rail being insulated from the ground and the current being
taken off by means of contact brushes or other devices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirl</ent>⟦br⟧
